{"title":"Standert updates its scandium alloy Kreissäge RS with aero features and more tyre clearance","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/standert-kreissage-rs-2025","date":1747296000000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/standert-kreissage-rs-2025\">Standert updates its scandium alloy Kreissäge RS with aero features and more tyre clearance</a></p>\n\n<p>Berlin-based Standert bikes has launched an aero update of its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-aluminium-road-bikes\">aluminium road bike</a>, the Kreissäge RS. Standert specialises in steel and alloy framesets and it uses its top spec scandium-aluminium alloy in the Kreissäge RS, which it says results in a 10% weight reduction over standard aluminium alloys.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kreissäge RS frameset is priced at €1,999, with a range of build options available with premium groupsets and wheelsets.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Now more aero</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"648\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-648x970.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-648x970.webp 648w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-200x300.webp 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-768x1150.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-1026x1536.webp 1026w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-1368x2048.webp 1368w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-750x1123.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-1140x1707.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08122-scaled.webp 1710w\" /><figcaption>Poster CA</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The original Kreissäge – meaning circular saw in German – was launched a decade ago now with the bike aimed at <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-praise-of-criteriums\">crit racing</a>, but also designed for all-round performance road riding.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Max Von Senger, CEO and founder of Standert, ‘The Kreissäge RS has always been about defining our own standards. It’s about showing what metal bikes can do, about being different in a sea of black plastic, and about having fun, while putting in the hard work.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Maxe Faschina, head of product at Standert adds, ‘We set out to create a faster aluminium frame, pushing both material and manufacturing limits.  A major redesign focussed on aerodynamics, especially up front, transitioning from a more traditional can-shaped headtube to a standout “hourglass” head tube — enhancing both speed and style.’</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+7\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'join us and discover the world's best places to ride, click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-7-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"648\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-648x970.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-648x970.webp 648w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-200x300.webp 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-768x1150.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-1026x1536.webp 1026w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-1368x2048.webp 1368w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-750x1123.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-1140x1707.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/standert_kreissaege_evo__poster_ca_com_DSC08133-scaled.webp 1710w\" /><figcaption>Poster CA</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Standert says it used CFD modelling to aero-optimise the head tube, top tube, down tube and seatstays of the new Kreissäge RS. The hourglass-shaped head tube, in particular, is claimed to result in a significant reduction in aerodynamic drag. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kreissäge RS frameset is hand built in Italy using custom Dedacciai scandium-aluminium alloy, in a tubeset that’s exclusive to Standert. Scandium alloys are renowned for their strength, which allows the frame tubing to be made thinner and hence lighter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new bike retains the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/road-bike-geometry-handling\">geometry </a>of its predecessor, but Standert says that everything else has been redesigned. That includes a new sloping top tube and a wider 86mm <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bottom-bracket-standards-guide\">T47 bottom bracket</a> shell to increase frameset rigidity. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tyre clearance has been increased to 35mm and there are now internal headset bearings that Standert says are lighter and should offer increased longevity. It offers a choice of either stainless steel or CeramicSpeed SLT self-lubricating bearings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Standert has also swapped to a UDH derailleur hanger and there’s full internal cable routing. </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/standert-pfadfinder-bike-review\">Standert Pfadfinder bike review</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-all-round-road-race-bikes\">Best all-round road race bikes 2025 reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-aluminium-road-bikes\">Best aluminium road bikes 2025 reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-steel-road-bike\">Best steel road bikes 2025 reviewed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">Best road bikes 2025 reviewed and rated</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Spec options and prices</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Standert will offer the Kreissäge RS with a range of top spec Shimano and SRAM <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-to-road-bike-groupsets\">groupsets </a>and with wheelset options from DT Swiss and Scope, with Pirelli tyres. There’s a choice of handlebars including carbon options. Seven sizes are available: 48, 50, 52, 54, 56, 58 and 60. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Kreissäge RS frameset is priced at €1,999. An Ultegra build with DT Swiss ARC 1400 wheels is priced from €6,299.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/standert-kreissage-rs-2025\">Standert updates its scandium alloy Kreissäge RS with aero features and more tyre clearance</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"3e20f4f619c3865a48bb1446894986bdc2428d1545795f14ac97b6aaf978e271","category":"Cycling"}